# Spring Boot Ultimate Production Rules - Resilience and Reliability (10 Rules)

1. Set explicit timeouts for all external HTTP, DB, cache, and messaging operations.
2. Use bounded retries with exponential backoff and jitter for transient failures.
3. Protect unstable dependencies with circuit breakers and fallback policies.
4. Implement bulkhead isolation for critical resources to contain cascading failures.
5. Use idempotency for critical write endpoints and external callback handlers.
6. Apply dead-letter queues and replay workflows for failed message processing.
7. Use graceful degradation when non-critical dependencies fail.
8. Implement startup and liveness checks that verify critical dependency readiness.
9. Design stateless service instances to support horizontal scaling and rapid recovery.
10. Regularly run chaos/failure drills for dependency outage, latency spike, and pod restart scenarios.
